From 5feef8fa712bfb9ab5aea11880b940506ac4ba13 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Warwick Brown <me@moonman.me.uk>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 18:49:50 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 3/6] phase 5-C1..C3: Darwin-native mntinfo + pkgcmd port
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Path C rewrite: replace the OpenSolaris mntinfo (getmntent/getmnttab
family) with a Darwin-native equivalent using getmntinfo(3) +
statfs(2). All 13 pkgcmd binaries now build and install: pkginfo,
pkgproto, pkgmk, pkgtrans, installf, pkgadd, pkgchk, pkginstall,
pkgname, pkgparam, pkgremove, pkgrm, pkgscripts.

libinst/mntinfo_darwin.c (new, replaces mntinfo.o on Darwin):
    ~40 functions of the mntinfo API implemented against
    getmntinfo(3). fs_tab is populated lazily on first query from
    the live kernel mount table. Filesystem-size, free/used blocks,
    inode counts, mount-point resolution, remote/served detection
    (nfs/smbfs/afpfs/webdav), and path-to-fsys lookup all work
    end-to-end. Solaris-specific concepts without a Darwin analogue
    (mount_client, unmount_client, use_srvr_map, cachefs backfs)
    return failure sentinels — consumers already treat that as a
    legitimate outcome.

hdrs/libinst.h:
    Include <sys/statvfs.h> so fsblkcnt_t is visible where the
    prototypes are declared. Re-type get_blk_*_n / get_inode_*_n /
    set_blk_used_n to use fsblkcnt_t (matches struct fstable field
    type) — the previous 'unsigned long' typedef mismatched Darwin's
    fsblkcnt_t = uint32_t on the ILP32 target. Sun's Solaris typedef
    happened to match; Darwin's does not.

libinst/Makefile.mk:
    Swap mntinfo.o for mntinfo_darwin.o. Also drop is_local_host.o
    (Solaris impl uses sysinfo(SI_HOSTNAME) — Darwin lacks it); the
    Darwin is_local_host lives inside mntinfo_darwin.c.

libpkg/darwin_openssl_stubs.c:
    Add pkg_passphrase_cb and strip_port stubs — both referenced by
    pkgcmds from the OpenSSL / pkgweb subsystem we stubbed earlier.

pkgcmds/pkgtrans/main.c:
    Guard signal(SIGPWR, ...) on defined(SIGPWR). Darwin doesn't ship
    the power-failure signal.

hdrs/darwin_stat_shim.h:
    Add fsblkcnt64_t / fsfilcnt64_t → non-64 typedefs (Solaris large-
    file duplicate types; Darwin's plain form is already 64-bit).

Runtime spot check: pkginfo, pkgparam, pkgadd, pkgrm, pkgtrans, pkgmk
all start and print usage cleanly. Signed-package + web-install paths
still route through darwin_openssl_stubs (fail cleanly with 'not
supported on this build'); real OpenSSL 3.x port scheduled Phase 5-C4.
